               <p>WILLIAM STOKES. I am a <rs id="t18260914-111-viclabel659" type="occupation">cheesemonger</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18260914-111-victim797 t18260914-111-viclabel659"></join>, and live in <placeName id="t18260914-111-crimeloc660">Edgware-road</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18260914-111-crimeloc660" type="placeName" value="Edgware-road"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18260914-111-crimeloc660" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18260914-111-off657 t18260914-111-crimeloc660"></join>; the prisoner was in my employ. On the 26th of July I missed 1s. 6d. from my till, while I was gone into the parlour to speak to a friend, leaving the prisoner and a customer in the shop; I gave to Mr. Barker 20s. worth of silver to mark that evening; I saw it after it was marked; and at half-past nine o'clock on Monday evening, when no one was present, I put six of them into the till; and in about half an hour I missed two of them; the prisoner had been serving in the shop, and it was his duty to give change out of the till; I charged him with it, and he at last produced the two marked shillings from his pocket; the rest of the marked money had been paid away; my wife paid the prisoner his wages, and might have paid him in some of it.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18260914-111-person798">
                  CHARLES 
                  BARKER
               <interp inst="t18260914-111-person798" type="surname" value="BARKER"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18260914-111-person798" type="given" value="CHARLES"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18260914-111-person798" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . Mr. Stokes gave me 20s. worth of silver to mark on Saturday evening, the 26th of August, I marked it with a C D and a cross; here are some that I marked.</p>
               <p>Cross-examined by Mr. BRODRICK. Q. Can you say how many shillings there were? - A. No; there was 20s. in amount.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18260914-111-person799">
                  HENRY 
                  STOWELL
               <interp inst="t18260914-111-person799" type="surname" value="STOWELL"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18260914-111-person799" type="given" value="HENRY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18260914-111-person799" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am an officer. I went to take the prisoner, but before I got there he had given these two shillings to his master; I found no more on him; he said they were the only two shillings he had, and he would give his master his week's wages to forgive him.</p>
